sentences: Choi Woo-shik (Korean: 최우식; born March 26, 1990) is a Korean–Canadian actor.
He first gained widespread recognition for his leading role in the film Set Me Free (2014).

He then co-starred in the films Train to Busan (2016) and Parasite (2019), both of which received international critical acclaim and success, with the latter of which winning the Palme d'Or at Cannes and the Academy Award for Best Picture.

In 2011, while at Simon Fraser University, then-21-year-old Choi was given permission by his parents to attend an acting audition in Korea, subsequently leading to him making his acting debut.
